label: obsolete_dwelling
definition: A material entity for accommodation, such as a building, part of a building, caravan, houseboat or other mobile home. A tent is not normally considered to be substantial.

label: obsolete_eaves
definition: A processed material that is the bottom edge of a roof.  The primary function of the eaves is to keep rain water off the walls and to prevent the ingress of water at the junction where the roof meets the wall.  The secondary function is to control solar penetration; the eaves overhang can be designed to adjust the building's solar heat gain to suit the local climate, the latitude and orientation of the building, refer to passive solar building design. The eaves overhang may also shelter openings to ventilate the roof space.

label: obsolete_blood specimen in vacutainer
definition: A blood specimen that is located in a vacutainer.

label: obsolete_arthropod attractor role
definition: A role of a material entity realized in drawing an arthropod in the direction of the material.

label: obsolete_BG-lure scent dispenser
definition: A device manufactured by BioGents that is designed for operation with the BG-Sentinel trap and releases an attractant that mimics the scent of human skin.

label: obsolete_New Jersey light trap
definition: A light trap that is designed to use motorized suction to trap arthropods in a collection bag once they approach the light attractant.
definition source: Cire. N. J. agrie. Exp. Stn. 1942 No.421 pp.8

label: obsolete_gravid trap
definition: An arthropod trap that is designed to collect gravid female arthropods or their eggs.

label: obsolete_encephalitis virus surveillance trap
alternative term: EVS trap catch | EVS light trap
definition: A light trap that uses carbon dioxide as attractant. The trap consists of a container of dry ice with holes in the bottom to allow the carbon dioxide to flow downward into a separate container, in which a motorized fan creates suction to collect arthropods.

label: obsolete_BG-Counter
definition: A device manufactured by BioGents that is designed to count mosquitoes passing through the device, differentiating the mosquitoes from other arthropods.

label: obsolete_Centers for Disease Control and Prevention light trap
definition: A light trap that is designed to use motorized suction to trap arthropods in a collection bag once they approach the light attractant. This trap is also designed to be lightweight and operate in environments in which electricity may be scarce.

label: obsolete_BG-Sentinel trap
definition: An arthropod trap that is manufactured by Biogents and is designed to attract arthropods through the use of a motorized fan to mimic convection currents produced by a human. The current also pulls arthropods into the trap, where a layer of gauze prevents the arthropods from escaping along with the air current.

label: obsolete_barrier trap
definition: An arthropod trap consisting of a static physical barrier designed to funnel arthropods in flight into a container.

label: obsolete_Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute light-suction trap
definition: A light trap that is designed to use motorized suction to trap arthropods in a collection bag once they approach the attractant. The light is supplied by an 8 watt tube, and the fan providing the suction has an 11-centimeter diameter.

label: obsolete_resting box trap
definition: An arthropod trap that consists of a box that is open on one end. The placement of the box and modifications to it are done in such a way that it becomes attractive to an arthropod as a place to rest during a period of inactivity.
definition source: Proceedings of the Eighty-Second Annual Meeting of the New Jersey Mosquito Control Association, Inc. 1989, pp 53-57.

label: obsolete_Shannon trap
definition: An arthropod trap that is made of cloth and netting and is designed to be suspended from above (e.g. from a tree). It is also designed so that the arthropod enters the trap from beneath, being attracted to some bait, and is prevented from escaping upward by the suspended cloth, which allows them to be collected from the upper interior of the trap.
definition source: The American Journal of Tropical Medicine and Hygiene, Volume s1-19, Issue 2, 1 Mar 1939, p. 131 - 140

label: obsolete_sticky trap
definition: An arthropod trap that is designed to capture arthropods resting on a surface by coating the surface with adhesive.

label: obsolete_artificial pit shelter
definition: An arthropod trap, consisting of a pit dug under the shelter of a plant, designed to provide a space for arthropods to rest and be collected.

label: obsolete_resting bucket
definition: An arthropod trap that consists of a bucket, which is lined with fabric and placed on its side, and a wet cloth inside the bucket. The placement of the box and modifications to it are done in such a way that it becomes attractive to an arthropod as a place to rest during a period of inactivity.

label: obsolete_Mosquito Magnet trap
definition: An arthropod trap that is powered by propane and is designed to emit a combination of carbon dioxide, heat, water, and oct-1-en-3-ol attractants while simultaneously using suction to trap arthropods.

label: obsolete_knockdown arthropod specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process that involves exposing arthropods to pesticide, then collecting them once they become dead or immobilized.
definition source: 38th Report East Malling Research Station 1949-50 , 1951, p.148

label: obsolete_MosquiTRAP
definition: A gravid trap consisting of an arthropod attractant and adhesive surface.

label: obsolete_sticky resting bucket
definition: An arthropod trap that consists of a bucket, which is lined with adhesive and placed on its side, and a wet cloth inside the bucket. The placement of the box and modifications to it are done in such a way that it becomes attractive to an arthropod as a place to rest during a period of inactivity. The trap is designed for arthropods to become caught in the adhesive so that they can be collected.

label: obsolete_light trap for indoor use
definition: A light trap designed to be placed inside a building.

label: obsolete_knockdown arthropod specimen collection by pyrethrum spray
definition: A knockdown arthropod specimen collection process in which the pesticide is pyrethrum.

label: obsolete_light trap
definition: An arthropod trap that uses light as an attractant.

label: obsolete_live arthropod specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process meant to collect live specimens.

label: obsolete_larval specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the larval stage.

label: obsolete_daytime arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs in the daytime.

label: obsolete_human-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is biting a human.

label: obsolete_ovitrap
definition: An arthropod trap that consists of a container holding a mesh layer above water and is designed to trap arthropods hatched from eggs dropped over the water by gravid females.

label: obsolete_human-biting indoor arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is biting a human inside a building.

label: obsolete_human-biting outdoor arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration designed to catch specimens that are in the process of biting a human outside a building.

label: obsolete_arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: A live arthropod specimen collection process that involves the use of an aspirator, a device which is brought to an arthropod and causes the arthropod to be drawn by suction into a container.

label: obsolete_arthropod resting in animal house specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that catches specimens resting inside an animal house.

label: obsolete_arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is resting outside a building during a period of inactivity.

label: obsolete_outlet window trap
definition: An arthropod trap that is positioned adjacent to a window of a building and is designed to collect arthropods flying out of the building.

label: obsolete_adult arthropod specimen collection process
definition: A live arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the adult stage.

label: obsolete_animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod is biting an animal.

label: obsolete_arthropod resting outdoors on artificial support specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod rests on a processed material such as a wall or furniture.

label: obsolete_light trap for outdoor use
definition: A light trap designed to be placed outside a building.

label: obsolete_arthropod trap
definition: A device designed to catch arthropods.

label: obsolete_arthropod specimen collection process
alternative term: field population catch | collection of arthropods
definition: A specimen collection process that has the objective of collecting arthropods as specimens.

label: obsolete_animal-biting outdoor arthropod specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An animal-biting arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that occurs outside a building.

label: obsolete_arthropod resting outdoors on natural support specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod resting outdoors specimen collection by aspiration that occurs while the arthropod rests on an unprocessed material such as a plant.

label: obsolete_aquatic arthropod specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process that has the objective of collecting mosquitoes from an aquatic environment.

label: obsolete_landing arthropod specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process that occurs while the arthropods land on a surface.
comment: For example, while they are landing on a human bait.

label: obsolete_hand-held sweep net
definition: A device that consists of a network of mesh and is designed to capture adult arthropods.
comment: Can be successfully used to catch resting or flying adult arthropods.  The net typically is mounted on a frame that is attached to a handle to increase the reach. [ISBN:9781402066658]

label: obsolete_trap for emerging adult arthropods
definition: An arthropod trap that is designed to trap an arthropod as it emerges from water at the beginning of its adult stage.
definition source: American Midland Naturalist, Vol. 97, No. 2 (Apr., 1977), pp. 381-389

label: obsolete_Centers for Disease Control and Prevention gravid trap
definition: A gravid trap that consists of a pan holding a hay infusion, motorized fan, and collection bag. This trap is designed to attract gravid female arthropods to the infused material, which would serve as an oviposition medium, and then draw them into the bag with the current generated by the fan.
definition source: VSMO:0001510 | J Am Mosq Control Assoc. 1988 Dec;4(4):536-8.
example of usage: The original trap CDC gravid trap (or gravid trap of Reiter) consists of a 3 inch diameter PVC inlet tube housing a 6 V motor, as used in CDC traps, on which is mounted a four-bladed 3 inch counter-clockwise fan. The inlet tube is clamped between two vertical wooden boards that fit over a black plastic box (18.5 x 14.0 x 6.5 inches). A plastic 12 inch long PVC chimney slots into the upper end of the inlet tube. The top half consists of three struts that fit into and support a netting collecting bag. For this the middle of the collecting bag is reinforced with a circular patch of denim cloth. The oviposition attractant is made by adding 1 lb of hay and 1 oz each of dried brewer's yeast and lactalbumen powder to 30 gallons of tap water. This infusion is allowed to mature for 5 days. This original gravid mosquito trap of Reiter suffers from certain limitations, namely up to 10% of the catch of adults is damaged by passing through the fan blades, and adults tend to die of desiccation. [ISBN:9781402066658]

label: obsolete_arthropod trap containing small non-human animal bait
alternative term: trap containing small non-human animal bait
definition: An arthropod trap that uses as attractant an animal that is not human and is the size of a chicken or smaller.
comment: Small non-human animals used as bait include chickens and other birds, rabbits, rodents, and dogs.

label: obsolete_dipper for arthropod immatures
alternative term: dipper for immatures | collection of larvae from dippers | collection of pupae from dippers
definition: A device that is designed for the collection of arthropod larvae or pupae from water and has the shape of a ladle or a pan.
comment: A dipper is a commonly used tool for collecting larvae and pupae from their aquatic development sites.  Dippers vary in size, shape and the material they are constructed from.  A variety of utensils have been used as dippers, e.g. soup ladles, rectangular enamel pie dishes, photographic trays, frying pans, plastic or enamel bowls, household metal strainers and spoons.  Volumes of water collected by the dipper can vary from 100 ml to more than 1 liter depending on the specific dipper used.  Dippers can be equipped with plastic or metal screen bottoms, or customized with long handles to increase their reach.\ [ISBN:9781402066658]"

label: obsolete_resting flight-capable arthropod specimen collection process
alternative term: collection of resting insects capable of flight
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process that occurs while an arthropod that is capable of flight is resting outdoors during a period of inactivity.

label: obsolete_free-standing window trap
definition: An arthropod trap that consists of a transparent window placed in a box that holds a liquid solution deadly to arthropods. This trap is designed to stop an arthropod in flight, causing it to fall into the liquid and die.
comment: For example, Jonsson developed a free-standing window trap consisting of a 16 x 20-cm perspex box, 16 cm high and divided in the middle by a 20 x 36-cm sheet of perspex (window).  The two compartments of the box are filled to a depth of about 12 cm with 4-6% formalin containing a few drops of detergent; in winter ethylene glycol can be added to prevent freezing.  One or two holes drilled in one side of the box at 12 cm and covered with fine netting prevent the trap overflowing after heavy rain.  Traps are mounted on aluminium poles.  Flying insects on hitting the transparent vertical plastic window fall into the formalin.  The window trap may catch vectors that are seeking a host or moving for other purposes." [ISBN:9781402066658]

label: obsolete_device for resting of adult arthropods for collection
alternative term: trap or shelter for resting adult arthropods
definition: A device that is designed to provide a solid surface that is attractive to an arthropod as a place to rest during a period of inactivity.
comment: Most commonly used to collect mosquitoes.

label: obsolete_arthropod resting in human house specimen collection by aspiration
definition: An arthropod specimen collection by aspiration that catches specimens resting inside a human house.

label: obsolete_baited net trap
definition: An arthropod trap designed to work with an animal (which could be human) inside a netted structure. This structure is designed so that an arthropod, attracted by the animal, can fly into the netted structure but can neither escape nor reach the animal.

label: obsolete_pupal specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the pupal stage.

label: obsolete_resting arthropod trap
definition: An arthropod trap that is designed to be attractive to an arthropod as a place to rest during a period of inactivity.

label: obsolete_UV light source
definition: A light source that provides UV light for use in a distant area using a delivery system.

label: obsolete_visible light source
definition: A light source that provides visible light for use in a distant area using a delivery system.

label: obsolete_insecticide resistance datum
definition: A data item that is about resistance to an insecticide.

label: obsolete_egg specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process in which the arthropods are in the embryo stage.

label: obsolete_organism identification datum
definition: A data item that is the specified output of an organism identification assay.

label: obsolete_well net for arthropod immatures
definition: A device that is designed for the collection of arthropod larvae or pupae from water and consists of a conical net.

label: obsolete_gravid female arthropod specimen collection process
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process that has the objective of collecting gravid female arthropods.

label: obsolete_arthropod collection process with automated identification
definition: An arthropod specimen collection process that involves a device that produces data specifying the types of arthropod collected.

label: obsolete_flying adult arthropod collection process by passive interception
definition: An adult arthropod specimen collection process that has the objective of collecting arthropods capable of flight, through the use of a barrier trap.
